<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="sa">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Learn संस्कृतम् with राहुल् | Lesson 2 </title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Sans:wght@0,300;0,400;0,500&family=Tiro+Sanskrit:ital@0;1&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
*,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
:root{--ink:#1a1208;--parchment:#faf6ef;--warm:#c8873a;--muted:#8a7560;--border:#e8dfd0}
body{font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;background:var(--parchment);color:var(--ink);line-height:1.6;padding:2rem}
.container{max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;background:#fff;padding:3rem;border:1px solid var(--border);box-shadow:0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)}

h1,h2,h3{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;margin-bottom:1.5rem}
h1{font-size:2.5rem;border-bottom:2px solid var(--warm);padding-bottom:1rem}
h2{font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--warm);margin-top:2.5rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}

.lesson-part{margin-bottom:3rem}
.sanskrit-text{font-family:'Tiro Sanskrit',serif;font-size:1.2rem;color:#000;display:block;margin-bottom:0.5rem}
.translation{color:var(--muted);font-style:italic;font-size:0.95rem;margin-bottom:1.2rem;display:block}

table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:1.5rem 0;font-size:0.9rem}
th,td{border:1px solid var(--border);padding:0.8rem;text-align:left}
th{background:#fcfaf7;font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-weight:700}
tr:nth-child(even){background:#faf9f7}

.highlight{color:var(--warm);font-weight:700}
.task-box{background:#fdfcf0;border-left:4px solid var(--warm);padding:1.5rem;margin:2rem 0}

@media(max-width:600px){.container{padding:1.5rem}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Lesson 01: </h1>
     <h2>Part 1: Grammar</h2>
        <span class="sanskrit-text">स्वराः त्रिविधाः भवन्ति | ह्रस्वः दीर्घः प्लुतश्च |</span>
        <span class="translation">Vowels are of 3 types: short, long and protracted.</span>
        <p>For common use: ह्रस्व (short) and दीर्घ (long). Ignore the third.</p>
    <section class="lesson-part">
       
        
</div>

</body>
</html>
